        <title>An Introvert&#x27;s Voice</title>
        <published>2020-08-30T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2020-08-30T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://argon17.github.io/posts/an-introverts-voice-20200830/"/>
        <id>https://argon17.github.io/posts/an-introverts-voice-20200830/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://argon17.github.io/posts/an-introverts-voice-20200830/">&lt;div class=&quot;columns is-vcentered&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;
Go outside and get some air, Mom told&lt;br&gt;
she thinks, I&#x27;m depressed,&lt;br&gt;
I should meet new people&lt;br&gt;
talk to them, chill with them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How do I tell her that&lt;br&gt;
initiating conversation is a hard stuff for me,&lt;br&gt;
I&#x27;m afraid, I might say something wrong&lt;br&gt;
I feel secure while expressing myself on pages.&lt;br&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mom doesn’t know, that I’m always lost&lt;br&gt;
in my incredible imaginations,&lt;br&gt;
I don&#x27;t want to be recognized socially&lt;br&gt;
but a little gesture of me existing would work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although I like to&lt;br&gt;
open up to my close ones,&lt;br&gt;
They are few, who makes me speak&lt;br&gt;
They&#x27;re the ones who never judge me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, I shut down my laptop&lt;br&gt;
changed clothes, took my earphones,&lt;br&gt;
And started walking fast&lt;br&gt;
trying best to avoid eye contacts.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
